>>4c87926a-a5da-46f0-8e9b-d30c91edbb5a
Welcome anon. Perhaps the most important concept to get your head around is that this is not a web site. A normal web site has a central server that supplies data to clients that connect with a browser. This place is not like that at all. It's a set of small data files (images, comments, metadata etc) shared among everybody using a peer-to-peer protocol. 

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitTorrent

The graphics are showing you details about this peer to peer network and how you're contributing. Left hand graphic is the number of peers available:

Connected: 24 - you are sending and receiving from 24 others on the network
Connectable: 1051 - how many are available to connect
Onion: 725 - this is how many users are using the TOR network. 
Local: 15 - not sure but may be users close to you by ISP
